==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbind
<hw>Un*bind"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*b⟦imac⟧nd")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Unbound</conjf>
<pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*bound")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Unbinding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>unbindan</ets>. See
<er>Un-</er>, and <er>Bind</er>.]</ety> <def>To remove a band from; to
set free from shackles or fastenings; to untie; to unfasten; to loose;
<as>as, <ex>unbind</ex> your fillets; to <ex>unbind</ex> a prisoner's
arms; to <ex>unbind</ex> a load</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbishop</ent>⟦br⟧
